 @{B}manfilt(1)@{UB}@{UU}                     @{B}ROM@{UB}@{UU} @{B}2.04@{UB}@{UU} @{B}only@{UB}@{UU}                     @{B}manfilt(1)@{UB}@{UU}
                                @{B}9@{UB}@{UU} @{B}January@{UB}@{UU} @{B}1996@{UB}@{UU}



 @{B}NAME@{UB}@{UU}
      manfilt - Strip or convert nroff tty sequences to ANSI/AmigaGuide
      sequences

 @{B}SYNOPSIS@{UB}@{UU}
      @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} [@{B}BOLD@{UB}@{UU}=@{U}<style>@{UB}@{UU}] [@{B}UL@{UB}@{UU}|@{B}UNDERLINE@{UB}@{UU}=@{U}<style>@{UB}@{UU}] [@{B}STRIP@{UB}@{UU}] [@{B}GUIDE@{UB}@{UU}] [@{B}V40@{UB}@{UU}]
              [@{B}PB@{UB}@{UU}|@{B}PAGEBREAK@{UB}@{UU}]

 @{B}DESCRIPTION@{UB}@{UU}
      @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} is a program which reads output by @{B}nroff@{UB}@{UU}, @{B}troff@{UB}@{UU} or @{B}groff@{UB}@{UU} for
      tty devices and converts the familiar `@{U}c@{UB}@{UU} BACKSPACE @{U}c@{UB}@{UU}' to either ANSI
      sequences or AmigaGuide sequences.

      @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} reads from standard input and outputs the converted text to
      standard output.

 @{B}OPTIONS@{UB}@{UU}
      The options supported by @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} are:

      @{B}BOLD@{UB}@{UU}       Specifies the @{U}style@{UB}@{UU} used for the @{B}nroff@{UB}@{UU} bold sequences ( `@{U}c@{UB}@{UU}
                 BACKSPACE @{U}c@{UB}@{UU}' ).

      @{B}UNDERLINE@{UB}@{UU}  Specifies the @{U}style@{UB}@{UU} used for the @{B}nroff@{UB}@{UU} underline sequences
                 ( `@{B}_@{UB}@{UU} BACKSPACE @{U}c@{UB}@{UU}' ).

      @{B}STRIP@{UB}@{UU}      Simply strip out all @{B}nroff@{UB}@{UU} sequences, and add no new ones.

      @{B}GUIDE@{UB}@{UU}      Use AmigaGuide control sequences instead of ANSI sequences.

      @{B}V40@{UB}@{UU}        Use AmigaGuide V40 commands. May create smaller and faster
                 guides.

      @{B}PAGEBREAK@{UB}@{UU}  Splits the resulting AmigaGuide into several sections
                 (nodes). A new section is created whenever a form feed
                 (ASCII code 12) is encountered on the input stream. This
                 switch will also generate a table of contents which may be
                 accessed by pressing the 'Contents' button of your
                 AmigaGuide viewer. Do not use this option if no form feeds
                 are present on the input stream.

      @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} currently supports these @{U}styles@{UB}@{UU}:

           0 - Plain.

           1 - Bold.

           2 - Italic.

           3 - Underline.

           4 - Inverse video.



                                    - 1 -                        Release 1.2
@ENDNODE
@NODE PAGE2 "Page 2"



 @{B}manfilt(1)@{UB}@{UU}                     @{B}ROM@{UB}@{UU} @{B}2.04@{UB}@{UU} @{B}only@{UB}@{UU}                     @{B}manfilt(1)@{UB}@{UU}
                                @{B}9@{UB}@{UU} @{B}January@{UB}@{UU} @{B}1996@{UB}@{UU}



 @{B}EXAMPLES@{UB}@{UU}
      These are the commands used to create the AmigaGuide and the ANSI
      versions of the manfilt document:

           @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}<manfilt.txt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}>manfilt.guide@{UB}@{UU} @{B}GUIDE@{UB}@{UU} @{B}PAGEBREAK@{UB}@{UU}

           @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}<manfilt.txt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}>manfilt.doc@{UB}@{UU}

      To change the default @{U}style@{UB}@{UU} of the underline font to italic, and to
      recreate the AmigaGuide file without splitting it, use:

           @{B}manfilt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}<manfilt.txt@{UB}@{UU} @{B}>manfilt.guide@{UB}@{UU} @{B}UNDERLINE=2@{UB}@{UU} @{B}GUIDE@{UB}@{UU}


 @{B}BUGS@{UB}@{UU}
      Notice that using the @{U}PAGEBREAK@{UB}@{UU} option on input without form feeds may
      (will?) cause the resulting AmigaGuide file to become corrupt.

 @{B}AUTHOR@{UB}@{UU}
      Nils Peter Sudmann (nilss@stud.cs.uit.no)


































                                    - 2 -                        Release 1.2
